# sway config for the thread_control_panel kiosk.
#
# sway is acting purely as a compositor here, not a tiling WM in any
# meaningful sense — it owns the DRM, applies the output transform that
# rotates the Waveshare's portrait panel to landscape, and runs cog as
# the single fullscreen client. We don't bind any keys (kiosk has no
# keyboard), don't show a status bar, and don't allow window switching.
#
# If you ever want to debug from a connected USB keyboard, see the
# commented bindsym block at the bottom.

# Rotate the panel — Waveshare 6.25" is natively portrait (720x1560), the
# UI is designed landscape. Use `transform 270` instead if 90 is the wrong
# direction.
output * transform 90

# No decorations / borders / status anywhere
default_border none
default_floating_border none
hide_edge_borders both
titlebar_padding 0
titlebar_border_thickness 0
font pango:monospace 0

# Hide the mouse cursor after 1s of inactivity (touch input doesn't show one).
seat * hide_cursor 1000

# Single-app kiosk: launch cog, then anything else gets fullscreened too
# (mostly defensive — there shouldn't be anything else).
exec /usr/bin/cog -P fdo http://localhost:8080
for_window [app_id=".*"] fullscreen enable

# Debug exit hatch — uncomment ONE of these blocks if you ever need to
# kill sway from a connected keyboard. Leave commented in production.
#
# bindsym Mod4+Shift+e exit
# bindsym Ctrl+Alt+Backspace exit
